57203 - Amarr HS Space Exploration Expert System <font size="14">Amarr HS Space Exploration</font>

This Expert System makes available skills enabling a capsuleer to fly a Magnate-class frigate fitted with basic travel, scanning and hacking equipment. It does not include the Cloaking skill and is therefore best suited for exploration of High Security space.

An Expert System is a remote, restricted artificial intelligence providing you with access to certain skills during the active rental period. As it is independent from your clone and your capsule, an active Expert System is not lost on pod death or clone jump.

<font size="14">Renting an Expert System</font>

Expert System rental licenses can be purchased securely on <url=https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/>https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/</url> using a variety of methods.

<font size="14">Activating an Expert System</font>

Activation of an Expert System is automatic upon redemption of the item by the specific capsuleer intending to use the service.

Expert Systems are a product developed by the PKN Interstellar consortium, made available over the HyperNet FTL communications network, and marketed by PKN Interstellar member corporations. An Expert System is a restricted AI based on artificial gelbrain technology. As the Expert System uses neural pathways based on those created by skill training or skill injection, it is compatible with capsule-ship interface and control systems. Real time command and control communication is achieved using dedicated FTL channels on PKN Interstellar's HyperNet.		 Standard Expert Systems

57578 - Grand Prix Interceptors Expert System <font size="14">Grand Prix Interceptors</font>

This Expert System makes available skills enabling a capsuleer to fly all Interceptor class ships. This is a promotional Expert System released to celebrate the Federation Grand Prix.

The temporary skills provided by this Expert System last for four days. This Expert System will expire on March 30, YC123.

An Expert System is a remote, restricted artificial intelligence providing you with access to certain skills during the active rental period. As it is independent from your clone and your capsule, an active Expert System is not lost on pod death or clone jump.

<font size="14">Renting an Expert System</font>

Expert System rental licenses can be purchased securely on <url=https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/>https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/</url> using a variety of methods.

<font size="14">Activating an Expert System</font>

Activation of an Expert System is automatic upon redemption of the item by the specific capsuleer intending to use the service.

Expert Systems are a product developed by the PKN Interstellar consortium, made available over the HyperNet FTL communications network, and marketed by PKN Interstellar member corporations. An Expert System is a restricted AI based on artificial gelbrain technology. As the Expert System uses neural pathways based on those created by skill training or skill injection, it is compatible with capsule-ship interface and control systems. Real time command and control communication is achieved using dedicated FTL channels on PKN Interstellar's HyperNet.		 Promotional Expert Systems

57622 - Emperor Doriam II Memorial During his short rule, Emperor Doriam II was known as a benevolent leader to his people, a peacemaker with the neighboring empires, and a stalwart enemy of the heretical Blood Raiders. Born Doriam Kor-Azor, he was elevated to the Golden Throne thanks to the support of the capsuleers Ecliptical, BlackViper, Grikl and Kileak in the Amarr Championships of YC105.

Doriam II strived to be a just leader for all the citizens of the Amarr Empire, demonstrating this commitment early in his reign by embarking on an extended tour to visit every inhabited planet within Amarr space to hear the concerns of local Holders and appear before their populace.

Viewed as a sympathetic successor to Heideran VII, Emperor Doriam II continued his predecessor's irenic stance towards the Amarr Empire's neighbors, including efforts to maintain the tenuous peace with the Minmatar Republic. His primary military interventions were directed towards the Blood Raider Covenant, including a major assault on the Blood Raider strongholds within the Bleak Lands by combined forces of the Amarr Navy and capsuleer loyalists.

The success of Doriam II's campaign against the Blood Raiders saw them driven from the Bleak Lands and the reassertion of imperial rule over the systems the cultists had occupied. However, this success was not to be without a price, as Doriam II was assassinated in the Imperial Palace on July 4th, YC107. While the killing was a great mystery for many years, the assassins are now believed to have been members of the "Red Chamberlain" Dochuta Karsoth's Blood Raider cultist cell.

This monument was erected in YC123 by the order of Royal Heir Ersilia Kor-Azor in memory of her uncle's leadership of House Kor-Azor and the Amarr Empire.		 Large Collidable Object

57625 - Project Discovery Phase Two Monument Project Discovery Phase Two began in July of YC119, following the extremely successful protein classification work of Phase One with a new exoplanets hunting program under the guidance of CONCORD's Chief of Deep Space Research, Professor Michel Mayor.

This phase of the project marked the official transfer of the Project Discovery mantle from the Sisters of EVE to a dedicated research division within the CONCORD Assembly.

Project Discovery Phase Two advanced the search for new exoplanets significantly in its nearly three year operational lifetime, as capsuleers contributed their expertise to the analysis of stellar light curves in search of planetary transits.

Project Discovery Phase Two came to an end on YC122.06.15 and was replaced by a new Phase Three Flow Cytometry project.

Please query the Phase Two Monument's database for records of those capsuleers who were elite research contributors to Project Discovery's light curve analysis work.

515960 The Standup L-Set EW Expert System I rig provides a means for structure operators to adjust hardware systems involved in electronic warfare command and control so as to improve the effective range and capacitor efficiency of EW systems installed on Upwell technology structures.

This rig decreases capacitor use and increases the optimal range and falloff of Standup Variable Spectrum ECM Jammers, Standup Target Painters, Standup Remote Sensor Dampeners, and Standup Weapon Disruptors fit to the rigged structure.

Standup is a proprietary system that uses a Structure Autonomous Nanoassembly Device (Upwell) containing integrated template software, a nanoassembler array and sufficient nanomass to enable the construction of a variety of service modules, structure modules and structure rigs when inserted into the appropriate slots on a structure built with Upwell technology.

Note: Only one rig of the same type, counting both tech variations, may be fitted at the same time on a structure. Warp to the City of God
Around 2,000 years ago, Emperor Zaragram II set out to get in touch with his supernatural self and built a new holy city in space: Mezagorm. The city's name literally translates to "Vision of God" but is commonly known as the "City of God". Its purpose was to complete the revision and eradication of many of the most sacred traditions of the Amarr, solidifying Emperor Zaragram II's divinity and new teachings. The city was constructed in space as a dedication to Zaragram's II greatness, unbound by any earthly fetters. Just as construction of the city was completed, Emperor Zaragram II was assassinated by his grandson out of pious opposition to his grandfathers heretical beliefs. The city was then laid waste and abandoned.		 <b><url=showinfo:5//30002999>Shastal</url>: City of God</b>

Warp to the Golgothan Fields
The largest space battle of the Minmatar Rebellion took place in the system of Ennur. Named the Golgothan Fields, the battlefield saw the largest force the Minmatar had ever put together fight a returning Amarr fleet that intended to sweep through the Minmatar core systems and quell the Great Rebellion once and for all. The Minmatar fought fiercely and bravely with the battle lasting for many long hours. Eventually the Minmatar needed to retreat and the Amarr claimed a victory. However, the Amarr fleet took heavy losses, with many of the Imperial Navy's largest ships destroyed or disabled, reducing their offensive strength. This pyrrhic victory for the Amarr was to lead to eventual Minmatar strategic victory in the Great Rebellion. Pirates have been sighted rummaging in the fields and we urge any travelers to proceed with caution.		 <b><url=showinfo:5//30002412>Ennur</url>: Golgothan Fields</b>

According to accident reports, a large container of multiple types of highly caustic and corrosive materials burst, allowing the chemicals to float and mix freely in the zero-g environment. In time this formed a highly toxic gas cloud in and around the station. Lai Dai later stepped back their ambitions in biotech and the R55 Colony has lain abandoned ever since.</i>

575247 Federation Grand Prix YC123 Federation Grand Prix YC123
575248 Welcome to the Federation Grand Prix!

Get to know New Eden in a way you may never have done before!

Brave the New Eden cluster's more dangerous spaces to learn the secrets of New Eden's past. This Grand Prix will take you North as far as the borders of Pure Blind, far enough East to feel the stellar winds from the Great Wildlands, and far enough South to plunge into Querious, with wonderful and historical sights and monuments to visit along the race routes.

After you've finished the original three challenge circuits you will open up the "Extra Lap" challenges, which are timed and endlessly repeatable, to compete for your name on the Route Monuments that will be placed at the Grand Prix Start Line. All aspiring racers must finish the introductory route first before attempting any time trials. Race timers will be kept by external judges and results will be announced when the Federation Grand Prix has finished.

The Grand Prix waypoints include numerous lowsec systems and the fastest routes may include some nullsec systems. By participating in the Federation Grand Prix you release and forever discharge any and all liability of the organizers for any and all damages incurred during the Federation Grand Prix		 <b>Welcome to the Federation Grand Prix!</b>

575256 <url=showinfo:5//30003522>Sarum Prime</url>: Mekhios Graveyard
Warp to the Mekhios Graveyard
A scattered battlefield of countless ships lies in silence over the planet of Mekhios. This battle of enormous proportions saw a massive Minmatar fleet fight against the Imperial Navy during the Minmatar Elder Fleet invasion. Legend has it that untold numbers of Minmatar pilots lost their lives in a split second after the then Jamyl Sarum appeared on the battlefield. She is believed to have used an ancient Terran superweapon to disintegrate the Minmatar fighters to dust, while the Amarr believe it was an act of divine intervention. There are still fragments of Naglfar-class dreadnoughts and Tempest-, Apocalypse- and Armageddon-class battleships on the field but all smaller ships seemingly had been turned to dust. Recently unveiled in the graveyard is a statue in honor of Empress Jamyl I and her deeds that fateful day.		 <b><url=showinfo:5//30003522>Sarum Prime</url>: Mekhios Graveyard</b>

575535 <font size="14">Grand Prix Interceptors</font>

This Expert System makes available skills enabling a capsuleer to fly all Interceptor class ships. This is a promotional Expert System released to celebrate the Federation Grand Prix.

The temporary skills provided by this Expert System last for four days. This Expert System will expire on March 30, YC123.

An Expert System is a remote, restricted artificial intelligence providing you with access to certain skills during the active rental period. As it is independent from your clone and your capsule, an active Expert System is not lost on pod death or clone jump.

<font size="14">Renting an Expert System</font>

Expert System rental licenses can be purchased securely on <url=https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/>https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/</url> using a variety of methods.

<font size="14">Activating an Expert System</font>

Activation of an Expert System is automatic upon redemption of the item by the specific capsuleer intending to use the service.

Expert Systems are a product developed by the PKN Interstellar consortium, made available over the HyperNet FTL communications network, and marketed by PKN Interstellar member corporations. An Expert System is a restricted AI based on artificial gelbrain technology. As the Expert System uses neural pathways based on those created by skill training or skill injection, it is compatible with capsule-ship interface and control systems. Real time command and control communication is achieved using dedicated FTL channels on PKN Interstellar's HyperNet.		 <font size="14"><b>Grand Prix Interceptors</b></font>

575589 In the moment of our greatest need, with savage enemies at the gates, Jamyl Sarum returned from the embrace of God to rescue her people from destruction in YC111.

Though Royal Heir Jamyl Sarum had undertaken the Rite of Shathol'Syn following the victory of Doriam Kor-Azor's champions in the Amarr Championships of YC105, the Elder Fleet invasion of YC111 so threatened Holy Amarr that divine intervention restored her to the temporal world. Jamyl Sarum's Holy Flotilla was able to destroy the Elder Fleet with a weapon of divine power and liberate Amarr from a terrible doom.

Acclaimed a divine savior by the Empire, Jamyl I was crowned Empress of Holy Amarr following the repulsion of the Minmatar Elder Fleet from the territories of the Amarr Empire. Since her untimely death and return to the embrace of God, Empress Jamyl I has also been known as "St. Jamyl the Liberator".

This monument has been erected within the graveyard of broken warships above Mekhios in memory of our great liberator Empress Jamyl I, that her heroic deeds never be forgotten or allowed to diminish in the passing of the ages.

575591 Emperor Doriam II Memorial Emperor Doriam II Memorial Name of item 57622 (Large Collidable Object)
575592 During his short rule, Emperor Doriam II was known as a benevolent leader to his people, a peacemaker with the neighboring empires, and a stalwart enemy of the heretical Blood Raiders. Born Doriam Kor-Azor, he was elevated to the Golden Throne thanks to the support of the capsuleers Ecliptical, BlackViper, Grikl and Kileak in the Amarr Championships of YC105.

Doriam II strived to be a just leader for all the citizens of the Amarr Empire, demonstrating this commitment early in his reign by embarking on an extended tour to visit every inhabited planet within Amarr space to hear the concerns of local Holders and appear before their populace.

Viewed as a sympathetic successor to Heideran VII, Emperor Doriam II continued his predecessor's irenic stance towards the Amarr Empire's neighbors, including efforts to maintain the tenuous peace with the Minmatar Republic. His primary military interventions were directed towards the Blood Raider Covenant, including a major assault on the Blood Raider strongholds within the Bleak Lands by combined forces of the Amarr Navy and capsuleer loyalists.

The success of Doriam II's campaign against the Blood Raiders saw them driven from the Bleak Lands and the reassertion of imperial rule over the systems the cultists had occupied. However, this success was not to be without a price, as Doriam II was assassinated in the Imperial Palace on July 4th, YC107. While the killing was a great mystery for many years, the assassins are now believed to have been members of the "Red Chamberlain" Dochuta Karsoth's Blood Raider cultist cell.

This monument was erected in YC123 by the order of Royal Heir Ersilia Kor-Azor in memory of her uncle's leadership of House Kor-Azor and the Amarr Empire. 575597 Project Discovery Phase Two Monument Project Discovery Phase Two Monument Name of item 57625 (Large Collidable Object)
575598 Project Discovery Phase Two began in July of YC119, following the extremely successful protein classification work of Phase One with a new exoplanets hunting program under the guidance of CONCORD's Chief of Deep Space Research, Professor Michel Mayor.

This phase of the project marked the official transfer of the Project Discovery mantle from the Sisters of EVE to a dedicated research division within the CONCORD Assembly.

Project Discovery Phase Two advanced the search for new exoplanets significantly in its nearly three year operational lifetime, as capsuleers contributed their expertise to the analysis of stellar light curves in search of planetary transits.

Project Discovery Phase Two came to an end on YC122.06.15 and was replaced by a new Phase Three Flow Cytometry project.

Please query the Phase Two Monument's database for records of those capsuleers who were elite research contributors to Project Discovery's light curve analysis work.

575762 <font size="14">Core Ship Operations</font>

This Expert System has been loaded with foundational ship operation skills, at the maximum level available for Alpha Clones. Every available ship benefits from most or all of those skills.

An Expert System is a remote, restricted artificial intelligence providing you with access to certain skills during the active rental period. As it is independent from your clone and your capsule, an active Expert System is not lost on pod death or clone jump.

<font size="14">Renting an Expert System</font>

Expert System rental licenses can be purchased securely on <url=https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/>https://secure.eveonline.com/Pilot-Services/</url> using a variety of methods.

<font size="14">Activating an Expert System</font>

Activation of an Expert System is automatic upon redemption of the item by the specific capsuleer intending to use the service.

Expert Systems are a product developed by the PKN Interstellar consortium, made available over the HyperNet FTL communications network, and marketed by PKN Interstellar member corporations. An Expert System is a restricted AI based on artificial gelbrain technology. As the Expert System uses neural pathways based on those created by skill training or skill injection, it is compatible with capsule-ship interface and control systems. Real time command and control communication is achieved using dedicated FTL channels on PKN Interstellar's HyperNet.		 <font size="14"><b>Core Ship Operations</b></font>
